{"content_type":"tech","visual_kind":"decision_map","title":"Behavioral Patterns","subtitle":"Route by behavior pressure — who decides what and when","eyebrow":"Pattern Family","panels":[{"heading":"Strategy","tag":"Algorithm","bullets":["Caller picks policy at runtime","Multiple implementations, one interface","No self-transition"]},{"heading":"Observer","tag":"Events","bullets":["One event, many subscribers","Push-based notification","Publisher doesn't know consumers"]},{"heading":"Command","tag":"Action","bullets":["Queue, undo, log, replay actions","Decouple intent from execution","Action has lifecycle"]},{"heading":"State","tag":"Lifecycle","bullets":["Object self-transitions internally","Behavior changes with state","Not caller's choice"]},{"heading":"Template","tag":"Skeleton","bullets":["Fixed flow, variable steps","Don't call us, we'll call you","Frozen order, open hooks"]},{"heading":"+ 5 More","tag":"Specialized","bullets":["Iterator — traversal abstraction","CoR — handler pipeline/escalation","Mediator — central hub coordination","Memento — snapshot undo","Visitor — add ops to stable types"]}],"footer":"Algorithm swap? → Strategy. Self-transition? → State. Action lifecycle? → Command. Event fan-out? → Observer.","output_path":"assets/design-pattern/images/behavioral-overview.png"}
